            <title>[FLINK-8415] Unprotected access to recordsToSend in LongRecordWriterThread#shutdown()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8415</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void shutdown() {
    running = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;;
    recordsToSend.complete(0L);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In other methods, access to recordsToSend is protected by synchronized keyword.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;shutdown() should do the same.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
